<title>Conjugate of a complex number</title>
<table>
<tabular>
<row header="yes">
<cell><alert>Definition 2.13</alert></cell>
</row>

<row>
<cell>The conjugate of a complex number z = x+iy is denoted by <m>\ \overline{z}</m> and is defined as <m>\ \overline{z}</m> = x-iy. It can be represented by the point (x, -y) which is the reflection of the point (x, y) about the x-axis.</cell>
</row>
</tabular>
</table>
